  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    NEFFICS Service Modelling Editor: Installation guide&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Purpose and functionality&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The NEFFICS Service Modelling Editor is available as a TomCat component. The current version allows the specification&#xD;
    of all the features of Business-SoaML:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Simple Service Contracts (including specification of Roles in the Service Contract)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Compound Service Contracts (including specification of aggregated Roles and Collaboration uses)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Services Architecture (including specification of Participants and Collaboration uses refereeing to&#xD;
        ServiceContracts).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The editor also has an export functionality that allows exporting to a SoaML model with a UML Profile. Specification of&#xD;
    service interfaces (i.e., Light-USDL) is, however, not currently implemented. It will be done in the next version.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The editor also provides support for the specification of Value Network:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Roles&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Tangible Deliverable Flows&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Intangible Deliverable Flows&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The editor is based on Oryx. Oryx started as an open-source, web-based BPMN editor. It allows us to provide a fully&#xD;
    open-source solution when it comes to models and editors developed in WP5.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Requirements and installation&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The editor is accessible directly on the web at &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://tomcat.thingml.org/backend/poem/repository&quot;>http://tomcat.thingml.org/backend/poem/repository&lt;/a> and thus&#xD;
    does not require any installation. The editor has been tested and works with FireFox.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    OpenID&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In order to be able to save the models that you create in the editor you must log in using an OpenID. This allows the&#xD;
    tool to create a&amp;nbsp;repository for your account&amp;nbsp;in which your private models are stored.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    OpenID is free and can be obtained from one of the sites listed at &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://openid.net/get-an-openid/&quot;>http://openid.net/get-an-openid/&lt;/a> for example &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://myid.net/&quot;>http://myid.net/&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>NB.&lt;/strong> If you do not&amp;nbsp;log in using an OpenID the models will only be kept in memory and will be lost&#xD;
    when you exit the browser.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
